  "prompt": "How do I print an application form on the OJAS website?",
  "response": "To print an application form from the OJAS (Online Job Application System) website, you can follow these general steps:\n\n1. **Visit the OJAS Website**: Open your web browser and go to the official OJAS website.\n\n2. **Log In**: If you have already registered and submitted your application, log in using your credentials (username and password).\n\n3. **Navigate to Application Status**: Look for a section like \"Application Status\" or \"My Applications.\" This is where you can find your submitted applications.\n\n4. **Select the Application**: Find the specific application for which you want to print the form. Click on it to open the details.\n\n5. **Print Option**: Look for an option such as \"Print Application\" or \"Download PDF.\" This may be a button or link on the page. Click it.\n\n6. **Printing the Document**: Once the document opens (or if it downloads as a PDF), you can use your browser\u2019s print function (usually Ctrl + P on Windows or Command + P on Mac) to print the form. Make sure your printer is connected and set up properly.\n\n7. **Check Print Settings**: Before printing, adjust any print settings if necessary, such as paper size and orientation.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, you may want to refer to the help section of the OJAS website or contact their support for assistance. Keep in mind that the steps might vary slightly based on updates to the website or specific application processes.",
